
    Deputy president Cyril Ramaphosa is the new ANC number One!Ramophosa emerged victorious at the party’s 54th elective conference at Nasrec Showgrounds in Joburg.IT WAS A CLOSE SHAVE – HE WON BY ONLY 79 VOTES.Ramaphosa got 2440 votes while his competitor, Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma won 2261.His victory sent his supporters wild with joy.It was not a winner take all victory for the Ramaphosa camp, however.WINNER: David Mabuza is the new deputy president of the ANC.
